# SEO Best Practices

## Core Principles
- Every page must have unique, descriptive `title` and `description` metadata
- Optimize for both search engines (Google) and users (readability)
- Support multiple languages (th + en) with proper locale structure

---

## Metadata Requirements

### 1. Page Titles
- **Format**: `[Page Title] | Serene Mind`
- **Length**: 50-60 characters (optimal for Google)
- **Content**: Include primary keyword near the beginning
- **Uniqueness**: Every page/post must have a unique title

Example:
```typescript
export async function generateMetadata(): Promise<Metadata> {
  return {
    title: 'Understanding Vipassana Meditation | Serene Mind',
    description: '...',
  }
}
```

### 2. Meta Descriptions
- **Length**: 150-160 characters
- **Content**: Clear summary that includes keywords naturally
- **Call-to-action**: Optional but helpful (e.g., "Learn more about...")
- **Uniqueness**: Each page must have unique description

### 3. Blog Posts
- Must use `generateMetadata()` to create dynamic metadata per post
- Include OpenGraph tags for social sharing
- Use post `title`, `excerpt`, `imageUrl`, `date`, `tags`

Example:
```typescript
export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const post = await getPostBySlug(id, lang)
  
  return {
    title: `${post.title} | Serene Mind`,
    description: post.excerpt,
    openGraph: {
      title: post.title,
      description: post.excerpt,
      type: 'article',
      images: [post.imageUrl],
    },
  }
}
```

